A letter of complaint

There are some standard phrases and expressions we can use when writing a letter of complaint. 
When you write a letter to a company or a store in which you complaint about a product, you want to be clear and polite.
You should begin your letter saying why you are writing it and stating the complaint. 
Next you should explain the issues and problems that you have with the product.
Finally, you should explain the actions the company or store should take to solve the problem.

Beginning

I'm writing to complain about the poor quality of your product.

I'm writing to say that I was disappointed with the service I received at your store.

I'm very disappointed with the quality of the product at your store.

Details of complain

There are several issues with your product.

There is a fault with the product I purchased from you.

There is a problem with the cable.

Action

